<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2 class="geolocation-title location-text">DAY 1 | ARRIVAL &amp; NORTHERN LIGHTS SAMI CAMP</h2>
<p>Your Inghams Representative will welcome you at Evenes Airport and take you by coach (just 45 minutes) to your chosen hotel in Harstad – either the <a data-udi="umb://document/7be32c8182f04a828182d051fe43bb18" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7be32c8182f04a828182d051fe43bb18}" title="Thon Hotel"><strong>Hotel Thon</strong></a> or <a data-udi="umb://document/0f81e0e90be042c4a9074b3abc35a1ee" href="/{localLink:umb://document/0f81e0e90be042c4a9074b3abc35a1ee}" title="Scandic Hotel"><strong>Hotel Scandic</strong></a> (formerly Rica). </p>
<p>After settling in, join us for an orientation walk around pretty <a data-udi="umb://document/32d5eaa2d11e4d228a79550b66ff210f" href="/{localLink:umb://document/32d5eaa2d11e4d228a79550b66ff210f}" title="Harstad - Arctic Fjord Adventure"><strong>Harstad</strong></a> including the harbour, market square, high street and spa, just to get your bearings.  Enjoy dinner and then set off by coach into the surrounding wintery landscape in search of the magical Northern Lights.  Being directly under the <strong>Aurora Borealis</strong> belt is said to improve your chances of seeing the <a data-udi="umb://document/280ef861622541caa4a7e53db8f83271" href="/{localLink:umb://document/280ef861622541caa4a7e53db8f83271}" title="Northern Lights"><strong>Northern Lights</strong></a> natural phenomenon! </p>
<p>You’ll visit a traditional <strong>‘Sami’ camp</strong>, where you’ll learn about much of the culture of the Sami people and their traditional, simple way of life.  Traditionally nomadic people, ancient folklore and legend play a strong part in the Sami people’s history, who believed the <strong>Northern Lights</strong> were a phenomenon caused by the energy of their ancestor’s souls flying across the sky!  At the camp, you’ll cosy up by the campfire of a traditional ‘Lavvu’ tent with a warming drink and story-telling as well as venturing outside of course to admiring the night sky.  Try an ‘Aurora Cocktail’, served in an ice glass, with some tasty traditional Sami snack.</p>
<h2 class="geolocation-title location-text">DAY 2 | SEA SAFARI &amp; UMAMI CULINARY EXPERIENCE</h2>
<p><img src="/media/13052844/01-rib-sea-safari-from-harstad.jpg" alt="Rib tour" width="859" height="341" /></p>
<p>After breakfast, you’ll set off on an exciting <strong>RIB boat</strong> sea safari onto the 46km-long <strong>Vågsfjorden</strong>, surrounded by one of Norway’s most scenic island archipelagos. There is an array of wildlife to look out for, including sea eagles, kittiwakes and other bird, so remember your binoculars and a camera!  The sheltered, calmer waters of the fjords, and the several informative stops along the way to explain how the land has changed since the Ice Age, the various wildlife and getting up close to the remote ‘bird island’, home to over 10,000 birds, make this is a highly enjoyable trip, suitable for all – the boat will go as fast or as slow as you wish!  A light lunch at a remote waterside cabin with panoramic views is included before returning to Harstad.<br /><br />You have an afternoon of leisure to explore Harstad, we recommend a visit to Harstad’s <strong>‘Grottebadet’</strong> indoor pool and spa (approx. £11 local charge) – the perfect place to relax after the morning’s thrills. <br /><br /><img src="/media/13052826/visitharstad_umami_sn_15.jpg" alt="Sami cooking" width="859" height="437" /><br /><br />This evening brings you an authentic dining experience in the way of a fantastic <strong>‘Umami’</strong> gourmet dinner. ‘Umami’ roughly translates as ‘tasty and delicious’ in Japanese and is known as ‘the fifth taste’, said to enhance the other four base flavours of sweet, salty, sour and bitter. Created by locally renowned chefs, Sigrid Rafaelsen and Kim Håvard Larsen, and served in a roof-top setting with spectacular views, this promises to be a very tasty and memorable experience.</p>
<h2 class="geolocation-title location-text">DAY 3 | HURTIGRUTEN CRUISE TO SENJA ISLAND</h2>
<p>Following breakfast, you’ll board one of the famous <strong>Hurtigruten ships</strong> for a relaxing 3-hour scenic cruise along the Vågsfjorden and north to the town of Finnsnes, passing the unique Norwegian scenery of snow-covered mountains protruding from the rich, dark blue waters of the fjords. </p>
<p>From Finnsnes, you’ll embark a coach tour on the spectacular island of Senja, following the coast on the famous National Tourist Route, recognised for its natural beauty. There will be photo-stops along the way at the Ersfjord and Tungesnet viewpoints, both accessible, as well as a break for an included lunch in the pretty, traditional fishing village of Hamn i Senja, with its panoramic Atlantic Ocean views, before returning to Finnsnes to catch the ‘express’ boat back to Harstad (approx. 90 minutes). Dinner tonight is taken at your hotel in Harstad.</p>
<h2 class="geolocation-title location-text">DAY 4 (for 3-night breaks Sun-Weds) | RETURN TO UK</h2>
<p>Guests on our 3-night adventure have the morning at leisure, before the coach leaves for Evenes Airport and your homebound flight.</p>
<h2 class="geolocation-title location-text">DAY 4 (for 4-night breaks Weds-Sun) | ‘HISTORIC HARSTAD’ TOUR &amp; RØKENES FARM FEAST</h2>
<p>You’ll take an historic tour of Harstad, including the amazing World War ll ‘Adolf Gun’, one of the world's largest land-based guns. Still located inside a military base, you are only able to visit the gun with our guide, who will explain the detailed and interesting history of the gun and the role the gun played during the war for the German army, and Harstad’s history as an ally to the British. Inside, the gun looks exactly like it could have done when it was left in 1945 with original machines and plenty of artefacts still in place.  You can even climb into the 46cm diameter barrel of the gun for a unique photo opportunity!</p>
<p>You will also visit the picturesque Trondenes Church, a tall white building, which has been on the edge of the Vågsfjorden for over 750yrs since 1250. Now a protected building, a visit inside to see the beautiful and richly-decorated interior, which reflects the church’s journey through time, is only possible with our guide.</p>
<p>Your final morning stop is Røkenes Manor and Farm, owned by ten generations of the Kulseng family since 1673, and now renowned for its culinary traditions. Enjoy a tour of the estate and a delicious buffet lunch.  The tour gives you insights and tales from its history, with a peak inside the historic building, originally a family home. Then the former cowshed - now a delightful banqueting hall - sets the scene for a memorable lunch feast, with a buffet of fresh local specialities.  After a leisurely lunch we head back to Harstad, for some free time to relax, or to treat yourself to a little shopping for souvenirs of this memorable trip before your transfer to the airport for your flight home.</p>
